Tom Kha Gai

Nam Pla Prik:
1/4 c fish sauce
10 green thai chiles, minced

In a small bowl, mix all ingredients, then set aside until ready to serve.

Broth:
6 c chicken stock
1 tsp palm sugar or dark brown sugar
5 kaffir lime leaves
4 garlic cloves, peeled and smashed
2 lemon grass stalks, tougher outer leaves removed, inner core roughly chopped
2 red thai bird chiles, halved
2" piece ginger, peeled and thinly sliced

In a 4 quart saucepan, combine the stock, sugar, lime leaves, garlic, lemongrass, chiles, and ginger. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to a simmer. Cook until reduced to 4 c, 30 min. Strain and return to the pot.

Soup:
1 lb boneless, skinless chicken breasts, halved lengthwise and thinly sliced
1 c enoki mushrooms
1 c canned straw mushrooms, halved
13oz can coconut milk
2 tbsp fish sauce
cilantro and mint leaves for garnish
nam pla prik for serving
lime wedges for serving

Return the broth to a simmer and add the chicken. Cook, skimming occasionally, until the chicken is opaque, 5 min. Add the enoki and straw mushrooms, coconut milk, and fish sauce, and continue to simmer until the chicken is cooked through and the mushrooms are tender, 5 min. 
